  <compounddef id="class_g_g___dtls_protocol" kind="class" language="C++" prot="public">
    <compoundname>GG_DtlsProtocol</compoundname>
    <briefdescription>
<para>DTLS processor that performans the DTLS handshake and encrypts/decrypts buffers once the handshake has succeeded. The object exposes a &quot;user side&quot; data source and data sink to communicate &quot;user data&quot; (typically an application or a library like CoAP), and a &quot;transport side&quot; data source and data sink to connect to a &quot;transport&quot; (typically a <ref refid="struct_g_g___datagram_socket" kindref="compound">GG_DatagramSocket</ref>) that will transmit and receive the DTLS records. The object uses a GG_TimerScheduler to create retransmission timers when needed. </para>
    </briefdescription>
